<p>After I had been two days in Egypt, my wound turned septic.  The stomach was purple &amp; had no feeling in it.  The poison only had to sink about an eighth of an inch to do the trick, &amp; the wound was discharging so much, that I smelt like four dead Turks. However I managed to pull through, was then X rayed, &amp; the bullet extracted from the outside of the right thigh.</p>
<p>After that I improved like a house <strike>of</strike> on fire, &amp; was sent to England (to heal up) in the "Karoola" which had been fitted out by the Commonwealth Government at Southampton as a super hospital ship. Unfortunately the vibration from the engines went clean through me, &amp; I was in agonies all the way. I simply lived on morphia &amp; aspirin, so that when I arrived here I was a regular death's head.</p>
